history.text: The movie is "Wonder Woman".  based on the character from the DC comics.
Hi - I was not given the name of the movie- do you know the name?
Oh there it is, never mind.
So, she is an immortal Amazon warrior..
LOL....many so!
The movie itself is a war movie and is set during WWI.
Have you seen Wonder woman?
Oh I see, that sounds pretty serious.
I haven't, but by the looks of this paragragh, it sounds great!
Apparently, it isn't as dark as it sounds and is brighter than the regular style of DC movies.
I have seen my share of war movies....not my favorite by any means, but it is interesting to learn about history.
So, apparently, it is set in Paris.
or starts with a setting in Paris.

Where Diana receives a plate with a photograph of herself and 
four men.  The photo having been taken during WWI.
Ahh, I like Paris - been there several times - perfect setting for a movie consedering the historical buildings of Paris.

Agreed!  Who wouldn't love Paris!!  
So, the plate forces her to recall her past.
Definitely sounds like an interesting movie - I will need to check it out.
And apparently, Dianna was born on a hidden island, the daughter of a Queen and raised on this hidden island inhabited by the Amazonian warrior women,

Also, it seems the movie itself will include much of the history, 
mythology and gods and goddesses and such.
Really....? That explains the title.
Exactly.
so originally, Dianna is forbidden to train as a warrior
She eventually convinces her mother to allow her sister to train her.

I see, I wonder why....diffirent time
 I suppose.
Later, as a young woman, she rescues an American pilot after his plane crashes.
Clever girl - good for her!
right!
So, soon following, as would be expected, the island is invaded by bad guys looking for the pilot.
Well - she certainly lives up to her Wonder Woman title.
She definitely does!!
But, we wouldn't have expected anything different from Wonder Woman, right?
Are you sure you haven't seen this movie - you sure know a lot about it:)
True - Wonder Woman has a reputation to maintain.
HA!  Well, I haven't.
And I'm definitely trying to avoid too many spoilers from these paragraphs!
Both for myself and for you!
Smile .....I appreciate that.
So, it sounds like there are great battle scenes and heroic action scenes!
Probably TONS of beautiful Amazon women!
Absolutely - definitely a movie with loads of action.

Not to mention, it received a 92% : 7.6/10 from Rotten to
matoes
And a Cinema Score of "A"
Is that right.....makes sense just from the description alone.
I thought so too!
So, I didn't realize this movie has been out since 2015.
Who plays Wonder Woman - do you know?
Gal Gadot
Hahaha.....seriously 2015?? OMG, I don't go to the movies much, nor keep up with the latest.

Apparently, I don't either. Interestingly enough, i
t falls in the "Drama" genre...  I would have called it an "Action" from the description.
But, I think I will rent this movie - sounds like it will be time well spend.
I agree!
I'm going to do the same!
Who wouldn't love a movie about a demi-god using love to fight war!
They should make another category that includes both Drama and Action.
Agreed!  Should be called Action Filled Drama!

uid2response.feedback: Overall, it was a pleasure chatting with the other Turker, not to mention informative!
